Summary of the content (concise, presentation-ready)
Title

Top: SQL Project Workflow
ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) — Prepare and structure data: data architecture, integration, cleansing, load, and modeling.

EDA (Exploratory Data Analysis) — Understand the data: basic queries, data profiling, simple aggregations, distinct values, date ranges.

Advanced Analytics — Answer business questions: complex queries, window functions, subqueries, reports, and predictive/segmentation analysis.

Middle: Exploratory vs Advanced Analytics (side-by-side)
Exploratory Data Analysis (blue)

Database Exploration: inspect tables, columns, and data types.

Dimensions Exploration: DISTINCT values, categories, and date min/max.

Measures Exploration: SUM, AVG, counts, big-number identification.

Date Exploration: MIN/MAX, DATEDIFF, time ranges.

Ranking & Magnitude: Top N, bottom N, and magnitude checks.

Advanced Analytics (orange)

Change-Over-Time Trends: totals and averages by time period.

Cumulative Analysis: running totals, moving averages using window functions.

Performance Analysis: current vs target comparisons, year-over-year deltas.

Part-to-Whole / Proportional: percentage of total by category.

Segmentation & Reporting: CASE WHEN categorization, segment buckets, Top N reporting.

Bottom: Key Learning Outcomes (icons + one-line descriptions)
Dimensions & Measures — Differentiate categorical vs numeric; choose aggregations appropriately.

Trends & Time Analysis — Detect patterns and seasonality; use date functions and windowing.

Performance Metrics — Compare current values to targets and historical baselines.

Segmentation & Proportions — Group data, create buckets, and compute part-to-whole percentages.

SQL Techniques — DISTINCT, GROUP BY, window functions, CASE WHEN, subqueries, and aggregations.
